{
  "title":"Body",
  "date":"2006-05-07 CST",
  "origin":"Funny Logic",
  "url":"text-body",
  "author":"Ryan X. Charles"
}



			
				<p>I asked my body what it thought about the meaning of life, but it just sort of sat there for a while, and then eventually repeated word for word something I had said the other day. So I said, &#8220;Don&#8217;t you have a mind of your own?&#8221; which of course made it start to cry. I was just being sarcastic, but it felt like I was being mean.</p>

		
		

